<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Elk Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0689816839/natilangofthe-20
">Love Flute</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Picture book illustrating the Native American story of how the elks brought the first courting flute to the Sioux.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0395845122/natilangofthe-20
">The Story of Blue Elk</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Children's book based on a Pueblo Indian legend about a special connection between an elk and a mute boy.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0452276500/natilangofthe-20
">Spirits of the Earth: A Guide to Native American Nature Symbols, Stories, and Ceremonies</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Book by a Karuk elder about the meanings of Indian animal spirits, including a chapter on elk.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of tales about American Indian elk and other animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>



